10.text:
Gentlemen, including Tom, seem to harbor some discomfort towards KORI-KORY;

Tom had been there for two months, recuperating his legs;

One day, Tom made a arrow for a six-year-old boy;

This arrow would shoot out an object when the wind blew;

The little boy was very interested;

Soon, many people gathered there, asking Tom to make more;

He agreed, and they happily played for nearly ten days;

Tom wore sandals from the shore;

One day, Marabou expressed interest in their craft;

Tom made a pair of sandals for him;

Marabou wore them around his neck like a strange necklace;

Women usually take care of weaving, also known as 'sewing';

The weaving process involves cutting down tree trunks, soaking them in shallow water for a few days to soften the bark, and then baking the bark to make it easy to peel and clean.
